A strike by 30,000 workers at South
African coal mines owned by companies including  Anglo American
Plc (AAL) ,  Xstrata Plc (XTA)  and Exxaro Resources Plc enters its fourth day.  More than 130,000 gold miners at companies including
 AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG) ,  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  and Harmony Gold Mining
Co. are expected to start striking tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
